# Backup (resticprofile + restic)

## Trigger Backup

# Run scheduled backup (as systemd service, respects 6h skip + disk/LAN checks)
sudo systemctl start resticprofile-backup@profile-rotating-backup.service

# Run NAS backup manually from terminal (bypasses 6h skip, needs LAN)
resticprofile -c ~/.config/resticprofile/profiles.yaml nas-term.backup

# Run homeoffice backup manually from terminal (needs USB disk connected)
resticprofile -c ~/.config/resticprofile/profiles.yaml homeoffice-term.backup

## Monitor

# Check backup status (what waybar shows)
~/.config/waybar/scripts/restic-status.sh

# View systemd timer schedule
systemctl list-timers 'resticprofile*'

# View last run logs
journalctl -u resticprofile-backup@profile-rotating-backup.service -e --no-pager

# View snapshots (also: click waybar backup icon)
resticprofile -c ~/.config/resticprofile/profiles.yaml nas-term.snapshots

## Profiles
# homeoffice     - USB disk backup (scheduled, auto-mount/unmount)
# nas            - NAS backup over LAN (scheduled)
# homeoffice-term - same as homeoffice but for manual terminal use
# nas-term       - same as nas but for manual terminal use
# rotating-backup group runs: homeoffice + nas (daily timer)

## Skip Logic
# Scheduled runs skip a profile if last backup was < 6 hours ago
# Manual -term profiles always run (no skip check)
